{"_id":"fMIj2SL8LtHVIy60","name":"A Denal Settlement","content":"<p>The Denal are unique among the Kubora for building out over the water of their marsh. Even the Utcin Kubora build traditional Kuboran round-houses on the edge of the bogs of Hohnam Marsh.</p>\n<p>Good wood is difficult to find on the marsh and most is brought from the hills that enclose it. The roughly worked plank floor of a Denal hut is built on boughs driven into the mud of the marsh-bed. Those boughs also serve as corner posts for the rest of the building, with lighter boughs added as cross-bracing to give the walls strength. Walls and roof are of reed thatch, the latter supported by a central pole.</p>\n<p>Running around each hut is a walkway and rough planks connect the huts to one another and to the communal raft. These can be kicked into the water in emergency to isolate the huts. Crude ladders run down into the water and it is here that the household’s curuglau (coracles) are tied up.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>See  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.9v3byttmdc0M5SDW]{VILLAGE of CLAN EDAK - GM MAP}  for GM map with location numbers.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>01 - Reed Beds  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.HN8D61gwSNypdSbT]{01 - Reed Beds}</p>\n<p>02 - Household Hut  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.hOCttm5JkWbdApte]{02 - Household Hut}</p>\n<p>03 - Shuntul Lodge  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.M7l3a44bIuYBRvol]{03 - Shuntul Lodge}</p>\n<p>04 - Clanhead's Hut  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.oQIO30zSi9oKhAWl]{04 - Clanhead's Hut}</p>\n<p>05 - Central 'Raft'  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.ZVHMIxfAKoR9hgWs]{05 - Central 'Raft'}</p>\n<p>06 - Heneryne's Island  @Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.USGE1PiqFAATOEvA]{06 - Heneryne's Island}</p>","img":"modules/heart-of-darkness/image_library/scenes/Heart_of_Darkness/denal_village.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.kP8PxrVlV5Aj5s2T","hash":"48bfdaa31d679b437f2f05b653ec46d552d71988"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm-adv-sos.journals.6iSsBhoexD6IAIlE"},"undefined":{"hash":"16f413505994ea0d58ec944bd54d63f292d834cc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zqjgdvunkh","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Denal Kubora","color":"#6e4307","sort":681250}}}
{"_id":"fpJLtSNXCA4xELOQ","name":"Wet walls and floor","content":"<h2>ENCOUNTER</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Water trickling along the floor of the passage as well as down the walls requires a random PC to make a <em><strong>STUMBLE</strong></em> roll (Failure: 50% chance of stumble into the Lower Level if a hole is convenient, or take <em><strong>B1</strong></em> to a lower body location and go prone.</li>\n<li>Creeping through the passages means this encounter is ignored.</li>\n<li>Jogging through a passage section when this is encountered means every jogging PC must make a <em><strong>STUMBLE</strong></em> roll.</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.0qxNeh8d2Qugupan","hash":"27e941d88f6e597c44d4f8714449bd7b78bfc62b"},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4r2k8xc6l","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Act VI:  The Hand of Crador","color":"#886c44","sort":2100000}}}
{"_id":"fsBFUlQB5NOJ6LUN","name":"Act II:  The Asawne","content":"<h2>Overview</h2>\n<p>The PCs arrive at a large Asawne Kubora village. They meet a number of people who add to their picture of Kutz and his fate. They also learn that their mission may have significance to the Kubora as well as to the Earl of Tormau.</p>\n<p>Finally they are offered help in continuing their journey in pursuit of the lost mercenary, nearer to the Heart of Darkness. (Asawne Kubora includes maps of the village of Gomas ‘Straight Arrow’ and its immediate surroundings).</p>\n<p>Scenes 1 &amp; 2 can be played in any order, but Scene 3 is best kept until last.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>The guides continue to paddle up river through most of the morning. Towards midday the north bank begins to look less densely forested and it is soon clear that stretches of the bank have been subject to primitive cultivation. Finally the boats come in sight of a Kuboran settlement on the north bank of the river. This is the Asawne village to which Acurdin has been commissioned to deliver the characters.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.WjOTwMxPFCvjwn1f]{Clan Gomas: Village}</p>\n<p>As the PCs approach the village groups of children appear on the bank looking blankly at the visitors. Clad in skins and rough cloth they already show some Arus – disfiguring their otherwise innocent faces. The PCs see that the village is a substantial clearing with a palisade facing the forest.</p>\n<p>There are a number of substantial round-houses within the village bounds and beyond the stockade the forest has been cleared for several hundred paces and thinned further than that.</p>\n<p>Acurdin and the other guides allow the boats to coast in towards to shore, and the crude dock fashioned there. He advises the PCs to keep their hands visible.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Scene 1:  Ardo of Guil</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.SnORsfqqTdtPbfqj]{Act II - Scene 1: Ardo of Guil}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Scene 2:  Making Friends?</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.taXiaGqk8TdpIILS]{Act II - Scene 2: Making Friends?}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Scene 3:  Hanuhn Gomas</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[heart-of-darkness.journals.intKFTZq3KGImvo6]{Act II - Scene 3: Hanuhn Gomas}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.GDFTJ4V7nbDxD8nW","hash":"48bfdaa31d679b437f2f05b653ec46d552d71988"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm-adv-sos.journals.6iSsBhoexD6IAIlE"},"undefined":{"hash":"16f413505994ea0d58ec944bd54d63f292d834cc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_6sup32vavy3","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Act II:  The Asawne","color":"#30832a","sort":100000}}}
{"_id":"fvaJFDbYqlLvoZBi","name":"_Credits","content":"<p>This work is derived from the PDF \"PERAN: HEART OF DARKNESS\" from Lythia.com (<a title=\"Heart of Darkness\" href=\"https://www.lythia.com/adventures/heart-of-darkness/\">https://www.lythia.com/adventures/heart-of-darkness/</a>), and has been adapted to Foundry VTT by Michael Gurley.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><strong>Original Writer:</strong></h2>\n<p>Alun Rees</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><strong>Original Contributors:</strong></h2>\n<p>Anders Bersten and his players</p>\n<p>Dan Bell and the HarnWriters Team</p>\n<p>the players at HarnCon8 and IviniaCon 2008</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><strong>Art:</strong></h2>\n<p>Jamys of Abrant:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Acurdin 'The Guide':  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Ardo of Guil:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Gomas 'Straight Arrow':  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Gedis the lost boy:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Denal Tenau and Denal Anghenfil:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Den Hapra:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Coln of Kutz:  Richard Luscheck, NPC illustration from original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> adventure</p>\n<p>Art Sponsor:  Richard Luscheck art sponsored by Anders Bersten</p>\n<p>Denia Tributary, Peran Forest, Lower Cataract, Upper Cataract, The Forest at Twilight, The Forest by Moonlight, Dawn Across the Denia Marsh, Deep in the Marsh, The Leavetaking, The Broken Lands, Eerie Green Limestone Walls, The Walls of the Place of the Hand, Limestone Passageway:  Alun Rees, included in original <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Crador Token:  Jay Sojdelius</p>\n<p>Jamys' Note:  Michael Gurley</p>\n<p>Belligerent Man-at-Arms:  Michael Gurley</p>\n<p>Kuboran Profiles:  Aaron Holt</p>\n<p>Top of the Cataract - Skull on stick:  public domain photo from Internet</p>\n<p>Denal Village:  Michael Gurley, public domain image from Internet, edited with LunaPic</p>\n<p>Actor Profiles (Gargun, King Gerf, Yelgri):  public domain images from Internet, derived from Medieval manuscripts, edited with Paint 3D</p>\n<p>The Suyari Emerge from the Dark:  Michael Gurley</p>\n<p>Hand of Crador (Theater of the Mind image):  Michael Gurley</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><strong>Maps:</strong></h2>\n<p>Denia River Valley:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Awawne Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Asawne River Camp:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Awawne Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Redoubt of Clan Gomas:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Awawne Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Denia Marshes - GM map:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Denal Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Denia Marshes - Poetic map:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Denal Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Village of Clan Edak map:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Denal Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Denal Marsh Village:  Michael Gurley, created with Dungeondraft, <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">based on original map by Alun Rees in <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Denal Kubora</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> article</span></p>\n<p>Place of the Hand exterior map:  Alun Rees, from <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Denal Kubora</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Hand of Crador (Ground and Lower level) maps:  Michael Gurley, drawn in GIMP, based on original maps by Alun Rees in <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Place of Farewells:  Michael Gurley, created with Dungeondraft</p>\n<p>Swampy Islands (background for Fight In The Mist scene):  Christian Zeuch, purchased on DTRPG</p>\n<p>White Stoat Inn:  Michael Gurley, created with Dungeondraft, based on original by Alun Rees in <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>White Stoat Inn</strong></span> article</p>\n<p>Denia River Travel (Battlemap):  Michael Gurley, created with Dungeondraft</p>\n<p>Heart of Darkness (passageway and chamber):  Michael Gurley, created with Dungeondraft, <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">based on original maps by Alun Rees in </span><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Heart of Darkness</strong></span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> article</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><strong>Thanks:</strong></h2>\n<p>N. Robin Crossby and Columbia Games for Hârn.</p>\n<p>Alun Rees, for his generosity, enthusiastic support, and many email communications to clarify and provide insight into his original thought process behind the adventure/campaign narrative.</p>\n<p>The playtest group for the Foundry version of this adventure:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Konnel Damiano - Lieam of Arthim (Huntsman)</li>\n<li>Joe Adams - Sir Letos Lamrend (Knight)</li>\n<li>Lisa Adams - Uldis of Harand (Squire)</li>\n<li>John - Grobyn of Spedra (Priest of Ilvir)</li>\n<li>Jamie - Uaine of the Asawne Kubora (Herbalist)</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>NOTICE:</strong></p>\n<p>This is a self published HârnFanon work, created by Alun Rees. It is a derivative work of material published by Columbia Games Inc. and is released for free distribution and personal use by Alun Rees without the permission or endorsement of N. Robin Crossby, his estate, or Columbia Games Inc.</p>\n<p>This document is available for download free from www.lythia.com.</p>\n<p>If you have been asked to pay for this document, either as a download or as a hard copy, you have been robbed.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.YTXYYifEt4z1JByq","hash":"82ff58b4b649ada28d712afea2a6ddb8f5f1a3b0"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm-adv-sos.journals.jD265XBaxaNbjYns"},"undefined":{"hash":"7f0efe3fe66296b6749fcbdb2bdf81609b5b6a64"},"cf":{"id":"temp_kb45tkx7pd9","path":"Heart of Darkness","color":"#ed961d","sort":300000}}}
{"_id":"gu17e71t82z08bQ0","name":"Lower Cataract","content":"","img":"modules/heart-of-darkness/image_library/scenes/Heart_of_Darkness/LowerCataract.png","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.dW7u45TKZk0K62wN","hash":"4827ce08cb30068d2add63bba9780056bb7f1f90"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3t0858bnqro","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Act III:  Further Upstream","color":"#4f86b0","sort":750000}}}
{"_id":"h25su4llOQ003IY4","name":"Denal Anghenfil ('Marsh Ogre')","content":"<p>Anghenfil are born with a deep torso and long limbs but develop as any other child through their early years. However their mind stops growing at the age of 5 or 6. Their bodies in comparison quickly outstrip those of others, and they are typically 7 or 8 feet tall with an extremely heavy build conferring enormous strength and stamina by their early teens. They remain hairless throughout a life that rarely exceeds 30 years.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[heart-of-darkness.actors.kXqpPNytwbGuT1of]{Marsh Ogre (generic)}</p>\n<p>While they lack the intelligence for sophisticated warfare they have an instinct for the hunt and stealth. They can sit still for hours in ambush and then spring to the attack as if they had just arrived at the fray. They swim like fish; the webs between their fingers and long toes allow them to speed through water. Their deep chests give them a phenomenal lung capacity and they can dive for minutes on end or sit in the deep mud of a reed bed for hours with their eyes and nose barely, and rarely, exposed. Many a group of unwelcome visitors that have made camp on what they took to be solid ground have been woken by several anghenfil erupting out of the reeds among them. Encounters with other Kubora have led to tales of ‘Marsh Ogres’ that have reached Rethemi taverns.</p>\n<p> </p>","img":"modules/heart-of-darkness/image_library/actors/NPCs/Heart%20of%20Darkness/Marsh_Ogre_01.PNG","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.13K4bHsErGuRl8br","hash":"48bfdaa31d679b437f2f05b653ec46d552d71988"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm-adv-sos.journals.6iSsBhoexD6IAIlE"},"undefined":{"hash":"16f413505994ea0d58ec944bd54d63f292d834cc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zqjgdvunkh","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Denal Kubora","color":"#6e4307","sort":400000}}}
{"_id":"hH05hx0koYUYIvep","name":"Place of Farewells","content":"<p>At the head of the Denia Cataract a clearing serves neighbouring tribes as a safe place for trade with the Denal. The path running from there, along the river’s edge, to the Place of Farewells, is clearly signposted with the skulls of animals and humans. To stray off the path is to invite attack.</p>\n<p>The Place of Farewells is a slab of limestone projecting out from the edge of the forest. It offers a view over a lagoon of open water some 400 paces across. The lagoon is bounded on all sides by packed reed beds between which breaks hint at routes into the marsh.</p>","img":"modules/heart-of-darkness/image_library/scenes/Heart_of_Darkness/ThePlaceOfFarewellsMap.PNG","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ItkUiCuYzC5zrPoM","hash":"2e520a91357bbef86e32b2350068506ce5ca8f18"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3t0858bnqro","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Act III:  Further Upstream","color":"#4f86b0","sort":1050000}}}
{"_id":"hOCttm5JkWbdApte","name":"02 - Household Hut","content":"<p>A household of between 5 and 7 can occupy one of these reed insulated huts. Reed mats cover the floor and walls and are also set across doorways and widows providing rough but effective insulation. Combined with the suspended ceramic fire pot, vented through the reed roof, they make the hut surprisingly cosy against the cold and damp of the marsh night. Wads of reed mats also provide bedding.</p>\n<p>There is no discrimination among the anghenfil, teanu or other Denal; they share the household of their birth or adopted parent. If the hut is too crowded then the surrounding walkways provides extra room in warmer months. In the winter the more body heat a hut can generate, the better.</p>","img":"modules/heart-of-darkness/image_library/scenes/Heart_of_Darkness/02%20Household%20Hut.PNG","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"x7bG2mHcyINoyNtL":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.5acmU0fzDDXP05e9","hash":"48bfdaa31d679b437f2f05b653ec46d552d71988"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm-adv-sos.journals.6iSsBhoexD6IAIlE"},"undefined":{"hash":"16f413505994ea0d58ec944bd54d63f292d834cc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zqjgdvunkh","path":"Heart of Darkness#/CF_SEP/Denal Kubora","color":"#6e4307","sort":687500}}}
